The President met with his National Security Council to discuss the situation in Iraq and the strategy to counter ISIL in Iraq and Syria. The President was briefed on the latest developments in Iraq, including the support to the Iraqi security forces and local tribal fighters in Anbar province. The President expressed strong support for Prime Minister Al-Abadi's efforts and welcomed the Iraqi Council of Ministers' decision to accelerate training and equipping of local tribes, expand recruitment into the Iraqi Army, train local police, and develop a plan to retake Ramadi. The participants in the meeting included several key officials from various departments and agencies.